3329,d&c,D&C,128,12,"Herein is glory and honor, and immortality and eternal life—The ordinance of baptism by water, to be immersed therein in order to answer to the likeness of the dead, that one principle might accord with the other; to be immersed in the water and come forth out of the water is in the likeness of the resurrection of the dead in coming forth out of their graves; hence, this ordinance was instituted to form a relationship with the ordinance of baptism for the dead, being in likeness of the dead.",herein is glory and honor and immortality and eternal life the ordinance of baptism by water to be immersed therein in order to answer to the likeness of the dead that one principle might accord with the other to be immersed in the water and come forth out of the water is in the likeness of the resurrection of the dead in coming forth out of their graves hence this ordinance was instituted to form a relationship with the ordinance of baptism for the dead being in likeness of the dead 
